cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is primarily focused on information retrieval (IR) modeling, which falls under the cs.IR sub-category. The paper also discusses improvements in training algorithms and optimization techniques, which are relevant to the cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of Gumbel-Softmax sampling and the comparison on benchmark datasets suggest relevance to the cs.CL (computational linguistics) sub-category. Finally, the potential application of the proposed model to image retrieval tasks suggests relevance to the cs.CV (computer vision) sub-category.
